==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rink
<hw>Rink</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot. <ets>renk</ets>,
<ets>rink</ets>, <ets>rynk</ets>, a course, a race; probably fr. AS.
<ets>hring</ets> a ring. See <er>Ring</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
smooth and level extent of ice marked off for the game of
curling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An artificial sheet of ice, generally under cover,
used for skating; also, a floor prepared for skating on with roller
skates, or a building with such a floor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rinker</ent>⟦br⟧
